PERFORMANCE
-----------
Current pipeline performance:
- Credit Agent: ~100ms (XGBoost)
- Risk Agent: ~2s (LLM + XGBoost)
- Fraud Agent: ~2s (LLM)
- Attestation Agent: ~1.5s (LLM)
- Monitoring Agent: ~2s (LLM)
- Lending Agent: ~1.5s (LLM)

Total: ~9 seconds per assessment

Optimization opportunities:
- Parallel LLM calls (Risk + Fraud simultaneously)
- Cache LLM responses for common patterns
- Use faster model (Llama 3.1 8B instead of 70B)
- Batch multiple assessments


LANGGRAPH VS OTHER FRAMEWORKS
------------------------------
LangChain: Sequential chains, less flexible than graphs
CrewAI: Higher level, less control over state flow
AutoGen: Conversational agents, not task-oriented
Semantic Kernel: Microsoft framework, similar to LangGraph
LangGraph: Best for stateful multi-agent DAGs


CONCLUSION
----------
LangGraph provides a clean, extensible architecture for Aurum's credit
assessment pipeline. The linear flow is simple but the framework supports
complex agent orchestration patterns as the system evolves.


